%% RHOAI Platform Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.4-ea.2/PLATFORM.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GW as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy, Gateway API)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth2/OIDC
    participant IDP as OAuth/OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP TLS
    participant Dashboard as odh-dashboard<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 1: User Dashboard Access (RHOAI 3.x Gateway API)

    User->>Router: (1) HTTPS/443
    Router->>GW: (2) HTTPS/443 (TLS terminate)
    GW->>AuthProxy: (3) ext_authz check (HTTPS/8443)
    AuthProxy->>IDP: (4) OAuth/OIDC validation (HTTPS/443)
    IDP-->>AuthProxy: Auth token validated
    AuthProxy-->>GW: Allow (set auth headers)
    GW->>KRBAC: (5) HTTPS via DestinationRule
    KRBAC->>Dashboard: (6) HTTP/8080 (X-Auth-Request-User)
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: (7) HTTPS/443 (impersonated)
    K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: Resource data
    Dashboard-->>User: HTML/JSON Response

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Model Inference (KServe InferenceService)

    participant Client as Client Application
    participant Istio as Istio Sidecar<br/>(proxyv2, mTLS)
    participant vLLM as vLLM / OVMS / MLServer<br/>8000/TCP HTTP

    Client->>GW: (1) HTTPS/443 (Bearer token)
    GW->>AuthProxy: (2) ext_authz check
    AuthProxy-->>GW: Auth decision
    GW->>Istio: (3) HTTPRoute -> backend (mTLS)
    Istio->>vLLM: (4) HTTP/8000 (plaintext within pod)
    vLLM-->>Client: (5) Inference Response

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Model Inference with Guardrails

    participant OrcGW as vllm-orchestrator-gateway<br/>8090/TCP HTTP
    participant Orchestrator as fms-guardrails-orchestrator<br/>8085/TCP HTTP
    participant Detector as guardrails-detectors<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant LLM as vLLM Backend<br/>8000/TCP HTTP

    Client->>OrcGW: (1) HTTP/8090 (chat completion)
    OrcGW->>Orchestrator: (2) HTTP/8085 (inject detector config)
    Orchestrator->>Detector: (3a) HTTP/8080 (content safety check)
    Detector-->>Orchestrator: Detection results
    Orchestrator->>LLM: (3b) HTTP/8000 (LLM generation)
    LLM-->>Orchestrator: Generated text
    Orchestrator-->>OrcGW: (4) Combined response (with fallback if triggered)
    OrcGW-->>Client: (5) Final response

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Data Science Pipeline Execution

    participant DSPApi as DSP API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB<br/>3306/TCP
    participant ArgoCtrl as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant StepPod as Pipeline Step Pod
    participant MLMD as ml-metadata<br/>8080/TCP gRPC
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    User->>DSPApi: (1) Create Pipeline Run
    DSPApi->>MariaDB: (2) Store pipeline/run metadata
    DSPApi->>ArgoCtrl: (3) Create Argo Workflow CR
    ArgoCtrl->>StepPod: (4) Create pipeline step pods
    StepPod->>MLMD: (5) Log artifacts (gRPC/8080)
    StepPod->>S3: (6) Store artifacts (HTTPS/443)
    StepPod-->>DSPApi: (7) Status updates

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 5: LLM Inference with KV-Cache Scheduling (llm-d)

    participant LLMDEPP as llm-d-inference-scheduler<br/>(EPP)
    participant PrefillPod as Prefill vLLM Pod
    participant DecodePod as Decode vLLM Pod

    Client->>GW: (1) HTTPS/443 via Gateway API
    GW->>LLMDEPP: (2) Ext-proc filter (hash prompt)
    Note right of LLMDEPP: Select pod by KV-cache affinity<br/>prefix cache hits, queue depth,<br/>LoRA affinity
    LLMDEPP-->>GW: Route to selected pod
    GW->>PrefillPod: (3) Forward to prefill pod
    PrefillPod->>DecodePod: (4) KV-cache transfer<br/>(NIXL/UCX or Redis)
    DecodePod-->>Client: (5) Streaming response
